{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":760,"text":"When I was first learning to meditate,"},{"time":2640,"text":"the instruction was to simply\npay attention to my breath,"},{"time":5720,"text":"and when my mind wandered,\nto bring it back."}]},{"cues":[{"time":8640,"text":"Sounded simple enough."},{"time":10680,"text":"Yet I'd sit on these silent retreats,"},{"time":13920,"text":"sweating through T-shirts\nin the middle of winter."},{"time":17280,"text":"I'd take naps every chance I got\nbecause it was really hard work."},{"time":20640,"text":"Actually, it was exhausting."},{"time":23400,"text":"The instruction was simple enough"},{"time":25160,"text":"but I was missing something\nreally important."}]},{"cues":[{"time":28320,"text":"So why is it so hard to pay attention?"},{"time":31080,"text":"Well, studies show"},{"time":32560,"text":"that even when we're really\ntrying to pay attention to something --"},{"time":35760,"text":"like maybe this talk --"},{"time":37360,"text":"at some point,"},{"time":38600,"text":"about half of us\nwill drift off into a daydream,"},{"time":40960,"text":"or have this urge\nto check our Twitter feed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":44360,"text":"So what's going on here?"},{"time":47000,"text":"It turns out that we're fighting one\nof the most evolutionarily-conserved"},{"time":50480,"text":"learning processes\ncurrently known in science,"},{"time":53360,"text":"one that's conserved"},{"time":54600,"text":"back to the most basic\nnervous systems known to man."}]},{"cues":[{"time":57840,"text":"This reward-based learning process"},{"time":59520,"text":"is called positive\nand negative reinforcement,"},{"time":61720,"text":"and basically goes like this."},{"time":64200,"text":"We see some food that looks good,"},{"time":65920,"text":"our brain says, \"Calories! ... Survival!\""},{"time":68640,"text":"We eat the food, we taste it --"},{"time":70160,"text":"it tastes good."},{"time":71400,"text":"And especially with sugar,"},{"time":72960,"text":"our bodies send a signal\nto our brain that says,"},{"time":75240,"text":"\"Remember what you're eating\nand where you found it.\""},{"time":79280,"text":"We lay down this context-dependent memory"},{"time":82040,"text":"and learn to repeat the process next time."},{"time":84520,"text":"See food,"},{"time":85760,"text":"eat food, feel good,"},{"time":87480,"text":"repeat."},{"time":88960,"text":"Trigger, behavior, reward."}]},{"cues":[{"time":91600,"text":"Simple, right?"},{"time":93920,"text":"Well, after a while,\nour creative brains say,"},{"time":96080,"text":"\"You know what?"},{"time":97320,"text":"You can use this for more\nthan just remembering where food is."},{"time":100960,"text":"You know, next time you feel bad,"},{"time":103160,"text":"why don't you try eating\nsomething good so you'll feel better?\""},{"time":107720,"text":"We thank our brains for the great idea,"},{"time":109760,"text":"try this and quickly learn"},{"time":111360,"text":"that if we eat chocolate or ice cream\nwhen we're mad or sad,"},{"time":114680,"text":"we feel better."}]},{"cues":[{"time":116640,"text":"Same process,"},{"time":118040,"text":"just a different trigger."},{"time":119800,"text":"Instead of this hunger signal\ncoming from our stomach,"},{"time":122920,"text":"this emotional signal -- feeling sad --"},{"time":124920,"text":"triggers that urge to eat."}]},{"cues":[{"time":127040,"text":"Maybe in our teenage years,"},{"time":129199,"text":"we were a nerd at school,"},{"time":131600,"text":"and we see those rebel kids\noutside smoking and we think,"},{"time":134320,"text":"\"Hey, I want to be cool.\""},{"time":135600,"text":"So we start smoking."},{"time":137800,"text":"The Marlboro Man wasn't a dork,\nand that was no accident."},{"time":141560,"text":"See cool,"},{"time":142800,"text":"smoke to be cool,"},{"time":144120,"text":"feel good. Repeat."},{"time":145960,"text":"Trigger, behavior, reward."},{"time":148640,"text":"And each time we do this,"},{"time":149920,"text":"we learn to repeat the process"},{"time":151960,"text":"and it becomes a habit."},{"time":153920,"text":"So later,"},{"time":155240,"text":"feeling stressed out triggers\nthat urge to smoke a cigarette"},{"time":158880,"text":"or to eat something sweet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":161200,"text":"Now, with these same brain processes,"},{"time":164160,"text":"we've gone from learning to survive"},{"time":166080,"text":"to literally killing ourselves\nwith these habits."},{"time":168960,"text":"Obesity and smoking"},{"time":170240,"text":"are among the leading preventable causes\nof morbidity and mortality in the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":175480,"text":"So back to my breath."},{"time":177720,"text":"What if instead of fighting our brains,"},{"time":180120,"text":"or trying to force ourselves\nto pay attention,"},{"time":182680,"text":"we instead tapped into this natural,\nreward-based learning process ..."},{"time":186720,"text":"but added a twist?"},{"time":188520,"text":"What if instead we just got really curious"},{"time":190600,"text":"about what was happening\nin our momentary experience?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":193120,"text":"I'll give you an example."},{"time":194680,"text":"In my lab,"},{"time":195920,"text":"we studied whether mindfulness training\ncould help people quit smoking."},{"time":199280,"text":"Now, just like trying to force myself\nto pay attention to my breath,"},{"time":202960,"text":"they could try to force\nthemselves to quit smoking."},{"time":206240,"text":"And the majority of them\nhad tried this before and failed --"},{"time":209200,"text":"on average, six times."}]},{"cues":[{"time":211960,"text":"Now, with mindfulness training,"},{"time":213480,"text":"we dropped the bit about forcing\nand instead focused on being curious."},{"time":217600,"text":"In fact, we even told them to smoke."},{"time":220840,"text":"What? Yeah, we said, \"Go ahead and smoke,"},{"time":222840,"text":"just be really curious\nabout what it's like when you do.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":226400,"text":"And what did they notice?"},{"time":228120,"text":"Well here's an example\nfrom one of our smokers."},{"time":230840,"text":"She said, \"Mindful smoking:"},{"time":232600,"text":"smells like stinky cheese"},{"time":234240,"text":"and tastes like chemicals,"},{"time":235880,"text":"YUCK!\""},{"time":237680,"text":"Now, she knew, cognitively\nthat smoking was bad for her,"},{"time":241080,"text":"that's why she joined our program."},{"time":243680,"text":"What she discovered just by being\ncuriously aware when she smoked"},{"time":248240,"text":"was that smoking tastes like shit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":251400,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":254360,"text":"Now, she moved from knowledge to wisdom."},{"time":258399,"text":"She moved from knowing in her head\nthat smoking was bad for her"},{"time":261519,"text":"to knowing it in her bones,"},{"time":264000,"text":"and the spell of smoking was broken."},{"time":266320,"text":"She started to become\ndisenchanted with her behavior."}]},{"cues":[{"time":270960,"text":"Now, the prefrontal cortex,"},{"time":273080,"text":"that youngest part of our brain\nfrom an evolutionary perspective,"},{"time":276640,"text":"it understands on an intellectual level\nthat we shouldn't smoke."},{"time":280720,"text":"And it tries its hardest\nto help us change our behavior,"},{"time":284560,"text":"to help us stop smoking,"},{"time":285920,"text":"to help us stop eating that second,\nthat third, that fourth cookie."},{"time":290960,"text":"We call this cognitive control."},{"time":292480,"text":"We're using cognition\nto control our behavior."},{"time":295960,"text":"Unfortunately,"},{"time":297200,"text":"this is also the first part of our brain"},{"time":299160,"text":"that goes offline\nwhen we get stressed out,"},{"time":301200,"text":"which isn't that helpful."}]},{"cues":[{"time":302480,"text":"Now, we can all relate to this\nin our own experience."},{"time":304981,"text":"We're much more likely to do things\nlike yell at our spouse or kids"},{"time":308160,"text":"when we're stressed out or tired,"},{"time":309800,"text":"even though we know\nit's not going to be helpful."},{"time":312160,"text":"We just can't help ourselves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":315120,"text":"When the prefrontal cortex goes offline,"},{"time":317320,"text":"we fall back into our old habits,"},{"time":319560,"text":"which is why this disenchantment\nis so important."},{"time":322440,"text":"Seeing what we get from our habits"},{"time":324120,"text":"helps us understand them\nat a deeper level --"},{"time":326320,"text":"to know it in our bones"},{"time":327600,"text":"so we don't have to force\nourselves to hold back"},{"time":329880,"text":"or restrain ourselves from behavior."},{"time":331640,"text":"We're just less interested\nin doing it in the first place."}]},{"cues":[{"time":334440,"text":"And this is what mindfulness is all about:"},{"time":337000,"text":"Seeing really clearly what we get\nwhen we get caught up in our behaviors,"},{"time":341560,"text":"becoming disenchanted on a visceral level"},{"time":345160,"text":"and from this disenchanted stance,\nnaturally letting go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":348920,"text":"This isn't to say that, poof,\nmagically we quit smoking."},{"time":352440,"text":"But over time, as we learn\nto see more and more clearly"},{"time":355080,"text":"the results of our actions,"},{"time":356440,"text":"we let go of old habits and form new ones."}]},{"cues":[{"time":360120,"text":"The paradox here"},{"time":361480,"text":"is that mindfulness is just\nabout being really interested"},{"time":364320,"text":"in getting close and personal"},{"time":365760,"text":"with what's actually happening\nin our bodies and minds"},{"time":368360,"text":"from moment to moment."},{"time":370000,"text":"This willingness\nto turn toward our experience"},{"time":372320,"text":"rather than trying to make unpleasant\ncravings go away as quickly as possible."},{"time":376760,"text":"And this willingness\nto turn toward our experience"},{"time":379360,"text":"is supported by curiosity,"},{"time":381240,"text":"which is naturally rewarding."}]},{"cues":[{"time":383000,"text":"What does curiosity feel like?"},{"time":384760,"text":"It feels good."},{"time":387040,"text":"And what happens when we get curious?"},{"time":389370,"text":"We start to notice that cravings\nare simply made up of body sensations --"},{"time":392840,"text":"oh, there's tightness, there's tension,"},{"time":395120,"text":"there's restlessness --"},{"time":396800,"text":"and that these body\nsensations come and go."},{"time":399880,"text":"These are bite-size pieces of experiences"},{"time":402880,"text":"that we can manage from moment to moment"},{"time":404920,"text":"rather than getting clobbered\nby this huge, scary craving"},{"time":409080,"text":"that we choke on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":410480,"text":"In other words, when we get curious,"},{"time":413000,"text":"we step out of our old,\nfear-based, reactive habit patterns,"},{"time":417760,"text":"and we step into being."},{"time":420000,"text":"We become this inner scientist"},{"time":422920,"text":"where we're eagerly awaiting\nthat next data point."}]},{"cues":[{"time":426160,"text":"Now, this might sound\ntoo simplistic to affect behavior."},{"time":430720,"text":"But in one study,\nwe found that mindfulness training"},{"time":433200,"text":"was twice as good as gold standard therapy\nat helping people quit smoking."},{"time":437120,"text":"So it actually works."}]},{"cues":[{"time":439800,"text":"And when we studied\nthe brains of experienced meditators,"},{"time":442640,"text":"we found that parts of a neural network\nof self-referential processing"},{"time":446480,"text":"called the default mode network"},{"time":448080,"text":"were at play."},{"time":449320,"text":"Now, one current hypothesis\nis that a region of this network,"},{"time":452280,"text":"called the posterior cingulate cortex,"},{"time":454520,"text":"is activated not necessarily\nby craving itself"},{"time":457280,"text":"but when we get caught up in it,\nwhen we get sucked in,"},{"time":459920,"text":"and it takes us for a ride."}]},{"cues":[{"time":461640,"text":"In contrast, when we let go --"},{"time":463760,"text":"step out of the process"},{"time":465160,"text":"just by being curiously aware\nof what's happening --"},{"time":467680,"text":"this same brain region quiets down."}]},{"cues":[{"time":471320,"text":"Now we're testing app and online-based\nmindfulness training programs"},{"time":475440,"text":"that target these core mechanisms"},{"time":478600,"text":"and, ironically, use the same technology\nthat's driving us to distraction"},{"time":483120,"text":"to help us step out\nof our unhealthy habit patterns"},{"time":485680,"text":"of smoking, of stress eating\nand other addictive behaviors."}]},{"cues":[{"time":489720,"text":"Now, remember that bit\nabout context-dependent memory?"},{"time":492320,"text":"We can deliver these tools\nto peoples' fingertips"},{"time":495240,"text":"in the contexts that matter most."},{"time":497520,"text":"So we can help them"},{"time":498760,"text":"tap into their inherent capacity\nto be curiously aware"},{"time":501760,"text":"right when that urge to smoke\nor stress eat or whatever arises."}]},{"cues":[{"time":506640,"text":"So if you don't smoke or stress eat,"},{"time":508480,"text":"maybe the next time you feel this urge\nto check your email when you're bored,"},{"time":512159,"text":"or you're trying to distract\nyourself from work,"},{"time":514423,"text":"or maybe to compulsively respond\nto that text message when you're driving,"},{"time":519080,"text":"see if you can tap into\nthis natural capacity,"},{"time":522960,"text":"just be curiously aware"},{"time":524240,"text":"of what's happening in your body\nand mind in that moment."},{"time":527200,"text":"It will just be another chance"},{"time":528680,"text":"to perpetuate one of our endless\nand exhaustive habit loops ..."},{"time":532360,"text":"or step out of it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":534080,"text":"Instead of see text message,\ncompulsively text back,"},{"time":537000,"text":"feel a little bit better --"},{"time":538760,"text":"notice the urge,"},{"time":540240,"text":"get curious,"},{"time":541720,"text":"feel the joy of letting go"},{"time":543680,"text":"and repeat."}]},{"cues":[{"time":545440,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":546680,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}